!Sample_data_processing = Short reads from C. globosum were aligned to the assembly of the Chaetomium globosum CBS 148.51 genome from the Broad Institute using TopHat v1.0.13. Reads from M. thermophila were aligned with BowTie v0.12.7 to the Sporotrichum thermophile genome assembly v2.0 from the DOE Joint Genome Institute, augmented with splice junction sequences. Introns were first located by mapping the pooled reads to the genomic sequence with BLAT; reads that aligned with >95% identity and coverage, but with gaps, were examined for the presence of plausible introns in the gaps. Splice junction sequences were constructed by concatenating 35 bases of sequence from the two flanks of the introns thus identified. Read alignments to the splice junction sequences were translated into gapped alignments to the genome. Reads that mapped equally well to more than one location were randomly assigned to one of the locations with probability proportional to the local depth of coverage by uniquely-mapped reads. Reads from T. terrestris were mapped to the Thielavia terrestris genome v2.0 from JGI.
!Sample_platform_id = GPL13173
!Sample_contact_name = Ian,,Reid
!Sample_contact_email = ian.reid@concordia.ca
